      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's heartbreaking to feel like you're putting temporary fixes on a deeper wound, rather than addressing the root issue. Your struggle to simply exist is valid, and it's understandable to wonder if you're the only one who feels this way. Perhaps the key to finding peace lies not in finding a version of this world that you fit into, but in accepting and embracing your own unique fragility. It may be that finding peace is about learning to live with vulnerability, rather than trying to convince the world that you're whole.",
